<% content_for :title, t("legal.terms.title") %>

<main class="legal">
  <header class="legal__header">
    <h1 class="legal__title"><%= t("legal.terms.title") %></h1>
    <p class="legal__updated"><%= t("legal.last_updated", date: "2026-04-19") %></p>
  </header>

  <section class="legal__section">
    <h2>1. The deal</h2>
    <p>
      Anon Wall is a hobby project. It lets people nearby leave short,
      anonymous notes for each other. There are no accounts and no
      profiles. By using it you agree to these terms. If you don't, close
      the tab.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal__section">
    <h2>2. You must be 18 or older</h2>
    <p>
      This service is intended for adults. By tapping "I'm 18 or older"
      you confirm that you are at least 18 years of age. If you are not,
      stop using the service.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal__section">
    <h2>3. What you may post</h2>
    <p>Keep notes short, anonymous, and human. Do not post:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Threats, harassment, hate speech, or sexualized content involving minors.</li>
      <li>Personal information about yourself or anyone else (names, phone numbers, addresses, workplaces).</li>
      <li>Spam, advertising, links, referral codes, or automated content.</li>
      <li>Anything illegal where you are, or anything that would put another person at risk.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to remove any note at any time and to block
      any session or device that abuses the wall.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal__section">
    <h2>4. Rate limits and duplicates</h2>
    <p>
      You can leave one note per minute, per session. Exact repeats are
      rejected. Notes fade away automatically after forty-eight hours.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal__section">
    <h2>5. No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      Anon Wall is provided "as is," with no guarantees of uptime,
      accuracy, retention, or fitness for any purpose. Don't rely on it
      for anything important. Don't use it to send messages you'd be
      upset to lose.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal__section">
    <h2>6. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      These terms may change. Continued use after a change means you
      accept the updated terms.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="legal__back">
    <%= link_to t("legal.back"), root_path %>
  </p>
</main>
